1. All fasteners should be installed as per recommended size with torque and torque mark (refer to installation manual). 2. M8*60 for the control box needs to maintain 10 Nm.

1. Ensure Drive Post is installed within tolerance 33 ± 25 mm. 2. The Maximum Height above the FGL for General Post and Drive Post should be maintained at 1138mm and 1171mm respectively. 3. For continuous slope, the open face of the general post should be higher side and web faces on the lower side. 4. Please refer GA drawing and Installation manual for Pile specifications & tolerances
1. Ensure the slew drive seat is installed at ±0° angle. 2. Ensure post & torque tube are installed as per GA drawing (Annex Exterior, Interior).

1. Ensure the post seat is installed concerning the slew drive seat angle. 2. Check and confirm bearing house is locked properly with plastic bearing arms. 3. Ensure M12 big plain washer is placed for slotted holes. 4. Ensure grounding cable is installed on both ends of the tracker and enough length is reserved for the full tracking range.

1. Check & confirm slew drive installed on correct piers. (refer to installation manual). 2. Check & confirm slew drives are aligned in a single axis from the initial reference. 3.Ensure the slew drive motor facing toward the south direction. 4.Ensure the motor is not impacted or damaged by external force. 5.Check & confirm motor dressing is properly done and reserved enough length at the binding & fixing point. 6.Ensure motor cable maintained more than 50mm bending radius.

1.Check and confirm the correct size torque tube installed(refer to GA drawing). 2.Torque sequence for the M12*45 bolt should start from the torque tube bottom and the angle difference is <0.5° at joint parts. 3.Ensure slew drive & torque tube connecting bolt M16X35 must use Loctite sealant for 4 threads without any debris. 4.Ensure TT alignment is properly aligned for tracker operations to reduce the overload on the motor. 5.Allowable torque tube tolerance from North to South is ±3 degree.

1.Check & confirm purlins are secured with Torque and Torque mark and U-Bolt thread is equally maintained. 2.Ensure the purlin gasket is placed. 3.Confirm purlin & gasket capsule slots are kept in the same direction throughout the tracker.

1.Check & confirm transmission shaft assembly installed and maintained proper length & alignment(refer to GA drawing). 2.Ensure the correct transmission shaft is installed. 3.Ensure all fasteners are torque & torque marked. 4.Check & confirm cotter pin is split and secured with the pivot pin.
1. Ensure the tube cover is placed on both ends of the tracker.
1.Grounding cables need to be installed in the two general posts at both ends of the tracker. 2.Check the other Grounding cable installed at the Control box

1.Ensure the AI Controller box is close to the Motor. 2.All accessories should be installed as per the installation manual without any damage. 3.Check and confirm the AI Controller box Emergency push button and DC Switch TURN-OFF. 4.Antenna should be placed at The south end of the torque tube. 5.Ensure proper cable routing & dressing are done for full tracker range operations.

1.Check & confirm Communication box and antenna Maximum height are maintained as per the Communication Installation manual. 2.The direction of the wind sensor Box face should be the North direction Assembly and the wind sensor direction should be a downside (Refer to installation manual for image) 3. Ensure cable dressing is properly done. 4. Check & confirm all fasteners are properly torque & torque marked. 5. Check & confirm proper earthing is done. 6. Ensure PU foam is applied to all cable glands.

1.Check & confirm module fasteners are secured with the proper torque and kept in stow position angle 0°. 2.Ensure from module edge to FGL 700mm gap is available for full tracker range operational. 3.Check & confirm grounding washer is placed on the same side of each panel. 4.Ensure modules are kept at 0° position after torque.

1.Check & confirm electrical wiring dressing is properly done from the PV string & Motor to AI-2 CB. 2.Ensure the DC extension cable & Y/T connectors are properly terminated (refer to the installation manual).
1.Check whether tracker rotation is happening properly as per design and specifications.
